      "name": "Medusa",
      "description": "Medusa is a ransomware-as-a-service (RaaS) group active in 2025, known for exploiting SimpleHelp RMM vulnerabilities to gain initial access, exfiltrate data, and encrypt victim systems. Medusa employs double extortion tactics and operates a dark web leak site.",
